<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fujimori: Gaviria Election Will Give OAS `Dynamism It Needs' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2903031594 Lima Global de Television Network in Spanish 
0100 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2903031594 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Global de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Remarks by President Alberto Fujimori in response to an </F>
unidentified reporter's question, place and date not given -- 
recorded] 
  [Text] [Reporter] What is your opinion, Mr. President, of 
[Colombian] President Cesar Gaviria's election as OAS secretary 
general? 
  [Fujimori] I want to reiterate here the opinion I have 
always 
held of President Gaviria. I believe that his tenure as 
secretary general will give the OAS the dynamism it needs in 
this process of modernization the whole world is undergoing. I 
think that in his capacity as future secretary general, he will 
lay great emphasis on regional integration, on economic and 
commercial development. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

