<F P=100> Suriname </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rebel Says Army Allegedly Allowed Rebels To Flee </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR2803145794 Amsterdam DE VOLKSKRANT in Dutch 28 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> BR2803145794 </F>
<F P=104>  Amsterdam DE VOLKSKRANT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Dutch </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Linda Otter: "`Surinamese Army Let Rebels Flee'"] </F>
  [Excerpt] Paramaribo -- During the recapture of the Afobaka 
Dam, the Surinamese Army deliberately gave all the rebels from 
the Suriname Liberation Front (SLF) the chance to flee. Nobody 
from the SLF was killed or wounded by the Army, said A. Bappa, 
one of the rebels involved in the occupation of the dam and the 
hostage-taking of 30 employees from the bauxite company Suralco. 
  This statement directly contradicts the Army's official 
statement, which said that five rebels were killed while fleeing 
during the recapture mission. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-12010 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat060_c_94002" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-LAT-94-060 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  28 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

