<H3> <TI>   Suspect Formally Arraigned in Colosio Killing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2903040194 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2903040194 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "ACIR Radio News" newscast] </F>
  [Excerpt] The Attorney General's Office has issued a 
bulletin explaining the charges filed against Mario Aburto 
Martinez and what will happen to him in terms of legal 
proceedings. Here is a report by Jesus Casasola: 
  [Begin Casasola recording] Mario Aburto Martinez has been 
formally arraigned without bail on charges of being responsible 
for the homicide of Luis Donaldo Colosio Murrieta, candidate of 
the Institutional Revolutionary Party. Judge Alejandro Ortiz, 
First District criminal judge of Mexico State, made the official 
announcement at Almoloya de Juarez Prison, where newsmen were 
not allowed access. The judge said Aburto Martinez is accused of 
carrying a weapon without a license, which means he could be 
sentenced to more than 55 years, considering the maximum 
sentence for homicide is 50 years. Aburto Martinez's lawyer has 
three working days to appeal the judge's decision to allow the 
normal course of the trial to continue. [sentence as heard] 
  The Attorney General's Office indicated that other charges 
could be brought against him as the investigations progress. The 
Attorney General's Office has also released reports on Aburto 
Martinez's medical and drug tests. A report on the 
reconstruction of the crime and an inspection of the crime scene 
was compiled on the same day and includes 163 photos. In 
addition, the ballistic and forensic report noted that the 
wounds were caused by a .38-caliber revolver. 
  According to preliminary statements by Aburto Martinez, he 
was not studying to be a priest, but he was to become a priest. 
He said he did not belong to any political party or group and 
that some people nicknamed him "Gentleman Eagle" [Caballero 
Aguila] because of a ring he wore on his left hand. 
  Another important aspect is the testimony of Marcelina Ortiz 
Martinez, who said that a few days before the killing the 
suspect told her he was about to make a good deal of money in 
the next few days. She added that he showed her a revolver, 
which was the same .38-caliber revolver he used to kill Colosio. 
It was also reported that Tranquilino Sanchez Venegas, arrested 
in Tijuana, Baja California, on Sunday, was not a member of 
Colosio's security guards headed by General Domiro Garcia Reyes. 
[passage omitted] [end recording] 

</TEXT>

