<H3> <TI>   New Antarctic Joint Command Head Installed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY3003034094 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1821 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY3003034094 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 28 Mar (NA) -- Lieutenant General 
Mario Candido Diaz, the chairman of the Armed Forces' Joint 
Chiefs of Staff, today installed Sea Captain Carlos Carbone as 
the new head of the Antarctic Joint Command in a ceremony held 
on the "Uruguay" corvette, which is riding at anchor at the 
Vuelta de Rocha in the Buenos Aires district of La Boca. 
  The new commander, who replaces Sea Captain Ricardo 
Corbetta, 
will be in charge of organizing the 1994-1995 Antarctic Campaign. 
  In his prior post as commander of the Argentine Navy's 
"Admiral Irizar" Antarctic vessel he commanded operations to 
resupply Argentina's Antarctic bases. 

</TEXT>

