<F P=106> [From the review of the 29 March issue of GRANMA] </F>
  [Excerpt] Good morning to all our listeners. On its front 
page, GRANMA carries remarks by Pedro Ross Leal, who says the 
response to the Parliaments in the Workplace assemblies cannot 
be just explanations but must be solutions. These assemblies sum 
up the workers' political line and the spirit that must be 
implemented, said Ross Leal at the end of the provincial 
assessment of the recommendations that will be submitted to the 
National Assembly [of the People's Government] by the workers 
movement. 
  The national committee of the Cuban Workers Federation [CTC] 
will meet this afternoon to analyze the ensemble of proposals 
made by Cuban workers throughout the country. 
  Another GRANMA article reports that the Republic of Cuba 
will 
decorate a group of outstanding youngsters from throughout the 
nation. These young people will receive the Order of Julio 
Antonio Mella and the Abel Santamaria and Jose Antonio 
Echeverria medals. This activity is part of the homage paid on 
the 32d and 33d anniversaries, respectively, of the Union of 
Young Communists [UJC] and Jose Marti Pioneers Organization. 
This ceremony will be held in San Pedro, Havana Province, the 
place where Jose Marti died. 
  Also, the objective of the Zambian foreign minister's visit 
to our country at the invitation of his Cuban counterpart is to 
prepare the forthcoming visit to Cuba by Zambia's president and 
to develop ties of cooperation between the two countries. 
