<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meeting on Regional Integration Begins </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2903222894 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2903222894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The second scientific meeting on Latin American 
integration called Inter-Lat-94 began today at the Cienfuegos 
Superior Technical Institute with the participation of 
approximately 100 delegates, among them Mexican and Ecuadoran 
guests. 
  At the opening session, Dr. Eduardo Cruz Gonzalez, dean of 
Cienfuegos University, said the objective of these meetings, the 
second of which is being held here in coordination with the 
Center for Research of World Economy, is to study how 
universities, in the midst of the difficulties daily affecting 
the world, can contribute to maintaining the concept of support 
to the integrationist process in America. 
  Several working groups are analyzing such topics as Latin 
American integration in history; the Latin American university 
in today's world; research on housing; and science, technology, 
and sustainable development. Two important seminars will close 
the international scientific research meeting on integration 
tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

