<H3> <TI>   Netherlands Explores Joint Business Ventures </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL3003014894 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL3003014894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Last week, the Netherlands-Cuba working group held 
its first plenary session. The business delegation, headed by 
(Coy Stork), was interested in contacting Cuban enterprises for 
research, coastal management and shoreline restoration in Cuba 
and the Caribbean, registration and joint operation of Cuban 
ships, construction in third countries, and joint productions in 
the machine tool, food, and textile industries. In exchange, the 
Netherlanders will supply canned milk, meat, fruit, and 
vegetables to Cuba. 
  In the 1994-95 work program, the group will promote 
possibilities for investment in Cuba and will support the 
efforts of Dutch enterprises established in Havana. The creation 
of joint enterprises and variants of associations of mutual 
benefit and the introduction of the scientific-technical, 
biotechnical, and pharmaceutical industries to the Netherlands 
market were additional aspects considered in the final document, 
which was signed by (Van Vough), head of the Dutch section, and 
Ariel Maso, director of (Cubanique) and head of the Cuban 
section at the meetings. 

</TEXT>

