<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Electric Union Repairs Breakdown at Power Plants </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2903230494 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in 
Spanish 0100 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2903230494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Given this past weekend's severe outages, the 
Electric Union advises that efforts to repair breakdowns at 
several power plants had already solved some problems by Sunday 
evening. Breakdowns in the generating units of the Talla Piedra 
and Regla power plants in Havana City, the East Havana power 
plant in Santa Cruz del Norte, as well as the Maximo [words 
indistinct] fuel supply to the Diez de Octubre Power Plant in 
Camaguey caused the elevated deficits that affected the early 
morning hours of Saturday and Sunday. The Electric Union told us 
they will return to the regular schedule in each province once 
the generating level has been recovered. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

