<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cardoso Accepts PSDB Presidential Nomination </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2903232394 Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network in Portuguese 
2200 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2903232394 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Finance Minister Fernando Henrique Cardoso has said 
that he is a candidate for president of the Republic. Minister 
Cardoso today received the PSDB [Brazilian Social Democracy 
Party] leaders. Speaking in the name of his party, PSDB 
President Tasso Jereissati invited Cardoso to become a 
presidential candidate. Jereissati said his party considers 
Cardoso's candidacy indispensable. 
  In his speech to the PSDB leaders, Minister Cardoso said he 
accepted the nomination and would carry the banner of victory 
because, according to him, it is the best way in which the 
economic plan can be complied with. 
  Cardoso said that the country is tired of corruption, 
inflation, and poverty. He told his PSDB colleagues that he 
will officially inform President Itamar Franco of his decision 
to step down from his ministry to become candidate for president 
of the Republic during the cabinet meeting that is taking place 
right now at Planalto Palace. 

</TEXT>

