<H3> <TI>   Economic Program To Be Platform </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY3003131394 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in 
Portuguese 1000 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY3003131394 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Corban Costa] </F>
  [Text] Fernando Henrique Cardoso bade farewell as finance 
minister to President Itamar Franco last night. He announced 
that his platform as a presidential candidate will be his 
economic plan. 
  Cardoso agreed to be the Brazilian Social Democracy Party 
presidential candidate during a meeting with party leaders 
yesterday. He will today hand the president of the Republic his 
resignation letter. Cardoso said the economic plan will not be 
changed by the installation of Ambassador Rubens Ricupero as the 
new finance minister. 
  [Begin Cardoso recording] He has already talked to the 
economic team and he is keeping them all in their positions. 
  We have high esteem for Minister Ricupero; we believe he 
will 
help very much in the implementation of the government action 
plan, which was proposed by me but is the government plan and 
belongs to the entire country. The plan will not be changed. 
[end recording] 
  Minister Fernando Henrique Cardoso will grant a news 
conference later today and then leave for Sao Paulo where he 
will spend the Holy Week holidays. 
  The new finance minister will be installed next week. 

</TEXT>

