<H3> <TI>   Fleury To Support PMDB Candidate, Not Cardoso </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY3003131494 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in 
Portuguese 1000 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY3003131494 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] After talking with Finance Minister Fernando 
Henrique Cardoso, Sao Paulo Governor Luiz Antonio Fleury Filho 
said he will not support Cardoso's presidential candidacy. He 
will instead support the Brazilian Democratic Movement Party 
[PMDB] candidate. 
  He favors holding primaries at the PMDB to choose a 
consensus 
candidate for the party. He added, however, that he will 
campaign for Orestes Quercia. 
  There are three candidates for the PMDB primaries: Orestes 
Quercia, Governor Roberto Requiao, and former President Jose 
Sarney, who is a senator. 

</TEXT>

