<H3> <TI>   PRD Leader Munoz Ledo Reacts to Nomination </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA3003034694 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0137 
GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA3003034694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "ACIR Radio News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Porfirio Munoz Ledo of the PRD [Party of the 
Democratic Revolution] has stated that in view of the country's 
circumstances, it is important for the government to be cautious 
because if it hardens its policy it will be risking the nation's 
social stability. Commenting on the nomination of Ernesto 
Zedillo Ponce de Leon as the PRI [Institutional Revolutionary 
Party] presidential candidate, the national PRD leader said that 
now more than ever, the political dialogue must be increased to 
guarantee clean elections. 
  [Begin Munoz Ledo recording] We hope that there will be no 
hardening of positions. The country's conditions make it 
advisable for the government to be cautious, wise, and tolerant. 
The Chiapas problem is not solved. There is concern and even 
emotional instability in vast areas of the country. We must 
advise the government to be cautious, increase political 
dialogue, and not allow the nomination of a candidate to be put 
on the same level with the appointment of a president. That 
would be the worst mistake that the system could make at this 
point. [end recording] 
  Munoz Ledo added that it is probable that Cuauhtemoc 
Cardenas 
will resume his campaign after Holy Week. 

</TEXT>

