<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tank Deployment Worries Cerrito Residents </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2903185294 Asuncion ABC COLOR in Spanish 29 Mar 94 p 10 </F>
<F P=103> PY2903185294 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion ABC COLOR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The unannounced deployment of tanks and soldiers 
from the regiments in Cerrito (Chaco) on 28 March caused unrest 
among Cerrito residents. The troops conducted exercises on 28 
March for about two hours near the regimental base. 
  In this regard, Colonel Carlos Medina Monjagata, the Armed 
Forces social communications director, reported that the tanks 
from the "Colonel Felipe Toledo" No. 2 Armored Cavalry Regiment 
were mobilized within the framework of a training exercise 
program for new recruits. 
  He explained that citizens were not informed about the 
mobilization because it was scheduled to be held in the vicinity 
of the regiment. He added: "The people are not informed when a 
two-hour exercise is held. They are informed only when tanks 
will cross the Paraguay River so that no one is alarmed." 
  Medina Monjagata stated that normally the recruits 
participate in two training exercises, the first during the 
basic training period and the second during the advanced program. 

</TEXT>

