<H3> <TI>   Officials Announce `Aggressive Mining' Strategy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2903175294 </F>
<F P=103> PA2903175294 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] Quito Voz de los Andes in Spanish at 
2300 GMT on 25 March reports that mining officials have 
announced that Ecuador is preparing to launch an "aggressive 
mining development" strategy with foreign funds. Santiago 
Cordovez, president of the Mining Chamber, pointed out that 
foreign mining companies plan to invest approximately $15 
million for exploration in 1994. If successful, plans call for 
over $20 million to be invested in exploitation by 1995. 

</TEXT>

