<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Nearly 10,000' Students Protest Attack on 26 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2602163794 Paris AFP in English 1519 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2602163794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, Feb 26 (AFP)--Nearly 10,000 Egyptian 
university students on Saturday denounced "Zionism" and demanded 
revenge for the massacre of 52 Muslim worshipers at a mosque in 
the Israeli- occupied West Bank. 
  The demonstrators, heeding a call by the Muslim 
fundamentalist-dominated student union at Cairo University, 
waved black flags and carried coffins draped in Palestinian 
flags. 
  Leaflets distributed by demonstrators called for "holy war" 
in support of the Palestinians, and said the "Muslim holy places 
in Palestine should be put under the protection of a 
fundamentalist state, such as Jordan." 
  They urged Egypt, the only Arab country to have a peace 
treaty with Israel, to break diplomatic relations with the 
Jewish state. 
  The campus was ringed by security forces to prevent any 
violence directed at the Israeli Embassy, only two kilometers 
(1.2 miles) away. 
  The Israeli Army said a lone settler, Barukh Goldstein, 
carried out the slaughter at the mosque in the West Bank town of 
Hebron Friday. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

