<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Protests Continue 27 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2702171694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1600 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2702171694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 27 Feb (MENA)--Cairo University students 
today continued their protests of the massacre in the Hebron 
Mosque, which left more than 60 Palestinians martyred and 
several others wounded at the hands of the terrorist Israeli 
groups. 
  More than 1,000 students organized a peaceful demonstration 
in which they shouted slogans denouncing the sinful aggression 
against the unarmed citizens and raised anti-Israeli signs. 
  Meanwhile, Cairo University has decided to cancel two Arabic 
musical concerts scheduled for today and to postpone until 3 
March a folk dance show by Rida Group, in solidarity with the 
families of the Palestinian martyrs and as an expression of 
denunciation for this appalling crime. 
  At Al-Azhar University students demonstrated today for half 
an hour while the opening session of an international 
competition on the Koran was held on campus. The students 
shouted slogans hostile to the Israeli practices and denounced 
the attack on worshipers at the Hebron Mosque early Friday. The 
students appealed to Arab and Islamic states to adopt a firm 
stance against the Israeli violations. 

</TEXT>

