<H3> <TI>   Consultative Council Condemns Hebron Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2602155994 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1400 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2602155994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] During its meeting this morning under the 
chairmanship of Dr. Mustafa Kamal Hilmi, the Consultative 
Council condemned the terrorist attack against Palestinian 
worshipers at the Ibrahimi Mosque in the West Bank yesterday. 
  Dr. Muhammad Zaki Abu-'Amir, minister of state for People's 
Assembly and Consultative Council affairs, described the 
incident as hideous and involved Palestinian brothers praying at 
the Ibrahimi Mosque. He affirmed that the Egyptian leadership 
has very strongly condemned this painful incident. 
  Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa has also announced that President 
Husni Mubarak was extremely disturbed by this incident and 
followed it up closely. He affirmed that the government 
condemns this crime and is closely following the situation to 
adopt what would be consistent with the public interest. He 
explained the importance of emphasizing that the Palestinians' 
security is a matter that must be given every consideration. He 
said all measures must be adopted to prevent a repetition of 
such incidents and to keep the future of peace from falling into 
the hands of the extremists and terrorists. 

</TEXT>

