<H3> <TI>   Awqaf Minister Comments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2602115894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1057 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2602115894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Al-Zaqaziq, 26 Feb (MENA)--Awqaf Minister Dr. 
Muhammad 'Ali Mahjub has condemned the massacre that occurred 
during the dawn prayers yesterday in the al-Ibrahimi Mosque in 
Hebron, West Bank. He called for placing the Jerusalem and the 
al-Aqsa Mosque issues on the list of urgent and essential issues 
that require a speedy solution. He appealed to the Islamic 
world, which is passing through one of its worst stages, 
particularly in Afghanistan and Somalia, to close ranks and 
stand up to preserve its standing and prestige. This statement 
was made at a popular rally held in the village of al-Sama'inah 
in Faqus District in al-Sharqiyah Governorate last evening. He 
noted that the goal of his tours of Egyptian governorates is to 
explain the facts to the people and to enlighten them about the 
dangers facing Egypt and threatening its security and stability. 
He noted that Egypt's stability ensures the stability of the 
Arab world, as Egypt is the safeguard of security and peace of 
the Islamic world. 

</TEXT>

