<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   AL-AHRAM Urges Security for Palestinians </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2702071294 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 0540 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2702071294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the press review] </F>
  [Text] On the Palestinian-Israeli negotiations, the 
newspaper AL-AHRAM writes in its editorial: The final round of 
these talks ended last Wednesday, having made important progress 
regarding formulating the final agreement. All indications 
showed that the Israeli withdrawal from Gaza and Jericho was to 
begin on the date which the two sides had agreed on. This 
deadline was set for 13 April. 
  However, everything changed suddenly after the horrific 
Hebron massacre. The venue of the negotiations stopped being of 
any consequence, be it Washington, Cairo, or Taba where Egypt 
was providing all possible support for the progress of the 
talks. What is important now is that the talks must focus on 
providing international protection for the Palestinian people 
and on taking the necessary measures to guarantee that the 
Israeli aggressors do not attack the peace-loving Palestinian 
people. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

