<F P=101> Kuwait </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Spokesman Comments on Hebron Incident </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502223994 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 2145 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2502223994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kuwait, 25 Feb (KUNA) -- Kuwait tonight denounced 
the hideous slaughter perpetrated by the Zionists in the 
al-Ibrahimi Mosque in occupied Hebron which led to the falling 
of scores of Palestinian martyrs and more than 200 injured. 
  A spokesman for the Kuwaiti Foreign Ministry told KUNA that 
this horrendous crime had moved the human feelings and 
conscience in Kuwait by its hideous and savage nature, and that 
denunciation is not enough to condemn this deliberate slaughter. 
He said that the Security Council and the superpowers in it are 
required more than ever before to take decisive and firm 
measures to protect the Palestinian people against such 
concocted crimes. 
  He added that by its protection of the settlements in the 
heart of the occupied Arab areas, the Israeli Government bears 
legal, material, and moral responsibility for this massacre. He 
said that while offering its sincerest condolences to the 
relatives of the martyrs and the Palestinian people, Kuwait 
believes that more international efforts should be made to 
secure the full Palestinian rights for setting up their own 
state on their national territory, because this is the sure 
guarantee for a safe future for them. 

</TEXT>

