Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Riyadh, 25 Feb -- The Kingdom of Saudi Arabia has 
condemned the massacre perpetrated at dawn today by Israeli 
settlers against Palestinians who were praying in the mosque of 
Abraham in Hebron. This massacre resulted in the deaths of 
dozens of people and the wounding of hundreds. 
  In a statement today to SPA, a responsible source expressed 
his condemnation and censure of this regrettable event, which 
bore the marks of extremism, fanaticism, and lack of respect for 
human rights on the part of the Israelis. 
  The source laid responsibility for this massacre on the 
Israeli Government because of its disregard for the crimes 
committed by Israeli settlers against unarmed Palestinians. He 
called on the international community to face up to its 
responsibility of providing protection for the Palestinians, who 
are suffering under the Israeli occupation, and of stopping 
these serious crimes and massacres against them. 
  In conclusion the statement indicates that this abominable 
crime might have a negative effect on the peace process in the 
Middle East. 

