<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rioting, Clashes Throughout Country Cause Casualties </TI></H3>
<H4>   Riots in Yafo, Nazareth, Other Israeli Towns </H4>
<F P=102> TA2602134394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1300 GMT 26 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2602134394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Arabs are rioting within the Green Line as well. 
In Yefet Street in Yafo, Arabs are rioting, throwing stones 
and attacking passersby. Our correspondent Shim'on Vilna'i 
reports the street has been blocked and the police are 
dispersing the rioters with tear gas. The windows of four 
police cars and three parking vehicles were smashed. The 
vehicle of Qol Yisra'el's correspondent was also attacked. 
  Meanwhile tempers have calmed down in Nazareth after the 
police dispersed the numerous rioters with tear gas. Our 
correspondent Yo'av Aviv reports that 40 residents were detained. 
  In the Wadi 'Ara road there are incidents of stone and 
bottle 
throwing at passing vehicles. 
  Five youths were detained in al-Tayyibah after they threw 
stones at policemen and Israeli vehicles. 
  There were also riots in the village of Baqa al-Gharbiyyah. 
Residents claim three local residents were slightly wounded by 
rubber bullets. 
  Today there are demonstrations and mourning processions in 
all the Arab villages within the Green Line. The demonstrators 
are calling for a separation between the two nations. Mourning 
processions are also being held in Haifa and East Jerusalem. 
  There were also riots at the entrances to the Temple Mount; 
four Arabs were detained. Youths who rioted in the Shu'fat 
refugee camp were dispersed with tear gas and rubber bullets. 
Our police affairs correspondent Aviv Bushinsky reports that 
youths gathered near Lions Gate and threw stones. They were 
also dispersed with tear gas and rubber bullets. 

</TEXT>

