<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Settlement Council Approves Inquiry </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2702142294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1400 GMT 27 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2702142294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Council of Jewish Settlements in Judaea, 
Samaria, and Gaza [CJSJSG] approves of the establishment of a 
state commission of inquiry into the Hebron killings, but at the 
same time demands that the commission check all the events in 
the six years of Arab terror. CJSJSG denounces the release of 
terrorists from prison, and opposes the proposals to seize 
weapons from Jews in the territories. Our correspondent Gil 
Litman reports that in a communique released today, CJSJSG once 
again expresses sorrow over the murders and denounces the 
killing of innocent people. 

</TEXT>

