<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Rabin Reacts to Hebron Incident </TI></H3>
<H4>   Compares Killer to Hamas, Islamic Jihad </H4>
<F P=102> TA2702190994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1800 GMT 27 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2702190994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Rabin made a comment about the 
massacre a short time ago in an address to the International 
Jewish Media Conference in Jerusalem. 
  [Begin Rabin recording] So far, we know that he did it on 
his own but I am also ashamed about others that came out 
publicly and supported his act. I believe that they represent a 
very small number of the people of Israel, even a small number 
among the settlers that oppose the policy of the present 
Government of Israel. He tried not just to kill innocent 
Palestinians while they were praying in a holy place. He joined 
with the Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] and the Islamic 
Jihad in the purpose to kill the peace negotiations. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

