<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Peres Reacts to Hebron Incident </TI></H3>
<H4>   Regrets PLO Suspension of Talks </H4>
<F P=102> TA2802093394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0900 GMT 28 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2802093394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres has expressed regret 
over the PLO's decision to put off the resumption of the 
negotiations with Israel. Peres told our correspondent Menahem 
Friedman that the government had approved tough steps against 
all manifestations of murder and violence or attempts to 
undermine the peace process. Foreign Minister Peres said there 
was a small group of people who posed a real danger to national 
security. The people who attended the murderer's funeral and 
shouted that he was a martyr pose a danger to Israel's future. 
The foreign minister nevertheless stressed that the 
Palestinians had no better alternative than resuming the peace 
process. 

</TEXT>

