<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Officials React To Hebron Incident </TI></H3>
<H4>   Tzaban, Rubinstein Back Anti-Kakh Moves </H4>
<F P=102> TA2602113894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 26 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2602113894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Minister Ya'ir Tzaban has said that in tomorrow's 
cabinet session he will again demand that all of the Kahanist 
organizations be outlawed and that the concentrations of 
settlers be moved out of Hebron. 
  Minister Amnon Rubinstein also said that tomorrow he will 
support the suggestions to outlaw Kakh members and supporters, 
to distance them from Qiryat Arba', disarm them, and not draft 
them to the IDF [Israel Defense Forces]. He told our 
correspondent Hayim Hecht that the upsetting remarks Kakh 
members made on Qol Yisra'el's weekly newsreel prove that the 
extremist settlers' moral standards have drastically 
deteriorated. 

</TEXT>

