<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Officials React To Hebron Incident </TI></H3>
<H4>   Bar'am Calls For Removing Settlers </H4>
<F P=102> TA2802110394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1000 GMT 28 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2802110394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tourism Minister 'Uzi Bar'am has demanded the 
immediate evacuation of all the settlers from Hebron, Bet 
Hadassah, Bet Romano, and Tall al-Rumaythah. Minister Bar'am 
estimated that another four or five cabinet ministers supported 
his position. In his opinion, yesterday's cabinet decisions 
were insufficient and did not meet the urgent need to halt a 
deterioration of the situation. Minister Bar'am was speaking in 
an interview to Qol Yisra'el. 
  Immigrant Absorption Minister Ya'ir Tzaban said that he had 
information that reserve IDF [Israel Defense Forces] officers 
were training groups from the Jewish Defense League, Kakh, and 
Kahana Hay in the United States. Tzaban told Qol Yisra'el that 
last year, the Kahana Hay movement had trained 200 youths in New 
York. Three graduates of that course arrived in Israel and 
embarked on violent tours of the territories. Minister Tzaban 
called for a ban on entry into Israel for members of these 
groups. 

</TEXT>

