<H3> <TI>   Zvili Sends 'Arafat Message of Condolences </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2602154994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1500 GMT 26 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2602154994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Labor Secretary General Nisim Zvili has sent a 
cable to Yasir 'Arafat stating he is shocked and horrified by 
the insane murder of innocent Palestinians at the Cave of the 
Patriarchs. Mr. Zvili emphasized the Israeli authorities are 
doing everything to prevent an exacerbation of the situation, 
and that the only way to break out of the circle of violence is 
to concentrate all efforts in order to facilitate the peace 
process. 
  Our party affairs correspondent Shmu'el Tal reports 
opposition leaders will convene this evening to consolidate 
positions in view of the possibility that the government will 
take advantage of the situation in order to facilitate the peace 
process. 

</TEXT>

