<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Islamic Extremists' Threaten Reprisals for Hebron </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2502175794 Paris AFP in English 1736 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2502175794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Gaza City, Feb 25 (AFP) -- Two Islamic 
fundamentalist groups threatened to kill more Jews in revenge 
for the massacre of 52 Palestinians by one or more settlers in a 
West Bank mosque on Friday. 
  'Izz-al-Din al-Qassam, the armed wing of the Islamic 
Resistance Movement HAMAS, warned: "Very soon Israel will be in 
mourning and put up black flags because 'Izz-al-Din will strike 
harder than even the Zionist terrorists can imagine." 
  Islamic Jihad said: "The blood of the people will not be 
shed 
for nothing. 
  "The bullets of the Islamic fighters will be our immediate 
answer to the Zionists." 
  In their statements, the fundamentalists joined the 
Palestine 
Liberation Organization's call for three days of mourning and a 
general strike throughout the occupied territories. 
  The mosque massacre sparked widespread clashes between 
Palestinians and Israeli troops who shot dead nine protestors 
and wounded scores more. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

