<H3> <TI>   Party Official: Coexistence With `Zionists' Impossible </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2602100494 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0900 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2602100494 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 26 Feb (INA)--'Abd-al-Ghani 'Abd-al-Ghafur, 
member of the Iraq Command of the Arab Socialist Ba'th Party and 
secretary general of the National Progressive and Patriotic 
Front [NPPF], has stressed that the Zionist massacre in which 
dozens of Palestinian worshipers were martyred and hundreds were 
wounded in the holy Ibrahimi Mosque in the city of Hebron has 
exposed the true nature of the Zionist plotting against the 
Palestinian people as well as the Zionist attempts to liquidate 
them and destroy their history and civilization. 
  In a statement to AL-JUMHURIYAH published today, 
'Abd-al-Ghani 'Abd-al-Ghafur said that this outrageous massacre 
shows the impossibility of coexistence between the Palestinian 
Arab people and the Zionists who usurped their land. 
  The NPPF secretary general called on the political forces 
and 
parties and human rights committees in the Arab homeland and the 
world to denounce and condemn this crime which the Zionist enemy 
would not have dared to perpetrate without the colonialist U.S. 
collusion with the Zionist enemy, and the continued U.S. support 
to enable it to carry out aggressions against the Palestine 
question, people, and civilization. 
  'Abd-al-Ghani 'Abd-al-Ghafur hailed the glorious sacrifices 
of the Palestinian Arab people, and expressed pride in the 
righteous martyrs and victims of the criminal act which was 
perpetrated by the Zionists against Palestinian worshipers at 
the Ibrahimi Mosque in the blessed month of Ramadan. 
  He noted that the escalation of the intifadah in the 
occupied 
Arab territories and the Palestinian people's continued 
confrontation of the colonialist Zionist schemes inside and 
outside the occupied territories constitute the only way to 
achieve the Palestinian people's national and inalienable 
objectives, and not the capitulatory framework in which the 
Zionists and colonialists have found their defeated dreams of 
entrenching their occupation of Palestine. 
  Concluding his statement, the NPPF secretary general 
stressed 
the support of Iraq, the NPPF parties, and the Iraqi people, 
under the leadership of President Saddam Husayn for the 
Palestinian Arab people's struggle to restore their national 
inalienable rights in their homeland. 

</TEXT>

