<H3> <TI>   Palestinian Camps on Strike Over Hebron Killings </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2702130994 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1915 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2702130994 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] A general strike was observed in all Palestinian 
camps in Syria to protest the bestial massacre perpetrated by 
Zionist settlers against our people in the holy Ibrahimi Mosque 
in Hebron. Shops were closed in these camps and black flags 
were raised to mourn the righteous Palestinian martyrs. 
  The factions affiliated with the Alliance of the Palestinian 
Forces in Syria decided to receive condolences for three days, 
as of today, Saturday, in the al-Yarmuk branch of the 
Palestinian Youths. 
  Palestinian popular organizations and masses today staged 
sit-ins at the offices of the International Red Cross, the 
United Nations, the Arab League, and the PLO in Damascus. They 
handed protest memorandums to the representatives of these 
organizations on this terrible massacre. The memorandums urged 
the international organizations and community to move swiftly to 
stop the massacres against the Palestinian people, to carry out 
their duties and safeguard the lives of innocent people, and to 
implement the international resolutions which call for 
protecting people under occupation. The Palestinian 
organizations' memorandums stressed that the new massacre will 
not prevent the Palestinian people from continuing their just 
struggle until they achieve all their objectives. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

