<H3> <TI>   Arab League Official Blames Israel for Hebron Massacre </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2702152794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1340 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2702152794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 27 Feb (MENA)--Arab League Assistant 
Secretary General 'Adnan 'Imran has stated that the world 
reactions to the massacre of Palestinian worshipers in the 
Hebron Mosque on Friday are not enough. He pointed out that the 
world community has gotten used to Israeli massacres. 
  Ambassador 'Imran noted that this is not the first and will 
not be the last massacre unless real international deterrent 
measures are taken. He pointed out that the Israeli settlement 
policy defies the Geneva Conventions and the UN Security Council 
resolutions. He added that this policy was not made by settlers 
but by the Israeli governments, which set up these settlements, 
are responsible for arming the settlers to seize Arab 
territories, and permitted them to use their weapons at their 
personal discretion. This, he added, shows that the Israeli 
authorities are responsible for writing the scenario of the 
massacre. 

</TEXT>

