<F P=100> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reply to PLO `Questions' to Determine Fate of Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2702171494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1600 GMT 27 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2702171494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Our correspondent Hayim Hecht reports that the PLO 
has sent the Israeli Government a series of questions about 
matters of principle. Israel's replies to these queries would 
help the organization decide its position regarding the 
continuation of the peace negotiations. The list of questions 
was handed to Major General Dani Rothschild by Palestinian 
delegate Sa'ib 'Urayqat. The questions deal with the 
confiscation of the settlers' weapons, the evacuation of the 
settlement of Netzarim in the Gaza Strip, and the stationing of 
an international force in the territories. 
  At today's cabinet session, Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres 
said that Israel could meet the Palestinian demands on certain 
issues; however, other demands, such as the stationing of an 
international force in the territories, would be rejected. 

</TEXT>

