<F P=100> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official: Approximately Half of Accord Finalized </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2602165194 Tel Aviv DAVAR in Hebrew 25 Feb 94 pp 1, 2 </F>
<F P=103> TA2602165194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv DAVAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Moti Bassok] </F>
  [Excerpt] This past week in Cairo, Yo'el Singer, the 
Foreign Ministry's legal adviser, and Nabil Sha'th, the head of 
the Palestinian delegation to the security committee talks, 
completed the formulation of approximately half of the overall 
agreement for Israel's withdrawal from Gaza and Jericho and 
settled the serious dispute over the Palestinians' legislative 
powers. In Singer's opinion, the meeting between Rabin and 
'Arafat and the signing of the agreement between Israel and the 
PLO could take place before 13 April 1994. 
  Nevertheless, in a special interview with DAVAR, Singer 
noted 
that Israel says that the mass release of prisoners is 
conditional on a general amnesty of collaborators. According to 
him, the PLO made a strategic decision to advance rapidly in all 
tracks of the talks. The talks in Cairo in the last two weeks 
have been very businesslike and good, Singer said. Issues which 
were previously settled only after arguments that lasted for 
days have recently been settled within half an hour, he said. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

