<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Reacts to Massacre at Hebron Mosque </TI></H3>
<H4>   Expresses Need for International Protection </H4>
<F P=102> LD2602205994 Paris France-2 Television Network in French 
1900 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2602205994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-2 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] [Announcer] Francois Mitterrand has written to 
Yitzhaq Rabin and Yasir 'Arafat. Bill Clinton has invited them 
to come to Washington again, but is not under any illusion for 
the time being. Yasir 'Arafat prefers to wait and see, as he 
told our correspondent in Tunis, Michel Montpontet: 
  [Begin recording 'Arafat in English with superimposed French 
translation; processed from the English] We are in need now of 
an international protection for our people. This is very 
important and the peace accord we have signed in Washington last 
September mentions an international presence, and the Israelis 
accepted that. Armed settlers are a real time bomb. We are 
asking the Israeli government to take measures, steps, and to 
take their responsibility, and to respect what they have signed. 
It is true that President Clinton offered us an invitation, but 
before that we would want to know under what umbrella. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

