<H3> <TI>   Al-Tibi Reports PLO Criticism of Cabinet Decisions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2702133794 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1300 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2702133794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Arab affairs correspondent Eldad Beck] </F>
  [Text] The PLO leadership in Tunis has already been 
apprised of today's cabinet session. The PLO declared that the 
cabinet's decisions were insufficient, failed to meet the 
Palestinians' minimum demands, and disappointing. We spoke with 
Dr. Ahmad al-Tibi, PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat's adviser, a short 
while ago. Dr. al-Tibi commented on the steps slated to be 
taken against the Kakh activists, including their disarmament. 
Al-Tibi said we are not dealing with a small group of people 
and asserted that a large number of settlers should be disarmed. 
Ahmad al-Tibi called for an immediate solution to the problem 
of the Jewish settlements, especially those located in the heart 
of Arab population centers. Al-Tibi said: A new era has ensued 
in the wake of the massacre in Hebron and the Israeli Government 
decisions do not meet its demands. In short, Ahmad al-Tibi 
described today's cabinet decisions as disappointing. 

</TEXT>

