<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Aides Say Majority Favors Continuing Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2602192494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1900 GMT 26 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2602192494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Most of Yasir 'Arafat's aides believe the peace 
process must be pursued, because halting the process would be 
tantamount to giving a prize to the insane murderer who acted in 
Hebron. This was said this evening by a senior source in the 
PLO leadership to our correspondent Moti Amir. He also said 
that tonight or tomorrow morning it will become clear whether 
the peace process will continue in its present format in 
Washington. The source emphasized Yasir 'Arafat is facing 
severe pressures by various PLO factions which are opposed to 
the continuation of the peace process, and is continuing his 
consultations in Tunis. 

</TEXT>

