<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO Envoy Calls on Israel to Disarm Settlers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502194694 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1845 
GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2502194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Due Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Remarks by Nimr Hammad, PLO representative to Italy, made </F>
while speaking to correspondent Michele Cucuzza on 25 February 
in Rome -- recorded] 
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] [Hammad] The settlers are 
responsible for this tragedy. This time the Israeli Government 
must make the brave decision to disarm the settlers and to 
clearly state that the settlements are illegal, and these 
settlers must be told that this land is occupied territory. If 
the Israeli Government does not make this decision, the entire 
peace process could lose its credibility. This will not only 
give rise to extremism, but the peace process will be refuted: 
Even the moderates will decide that it is meaningless. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

