<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arab League Envoy Urges Removal of Settlements </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2602160594 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1217 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2602160594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 26 Feb (MENA)--Harun Hashim Rashid, alternate 
Palestinian delegate to the Arab League, today said that the 
emergency meeting that the Arab League Council will hold 
tomorrow night, Sunday, will focus on the developments in the 
region following yesterday's massacre in the Ibrahimi Mosque. 
  Rashid told MENA that the Palestinian delegation will call 
on 
the Arab League to take a unified stance in the face of repeated 
acts of aggression by the Israeli settlers and Army. The 
Palestinians will also urge international protection of the 
Palestinian people for security and stability to prevail and as 
a necessary condition for pursuing efforts to achieve a just and 
comprehensive peace, Rashid said. 
  Rashid said that the Palestinians will also call for the 
presence of Israeli settlements in the occupied Arab territories 
to be reconsidered. He added that there is a need to remove 
these settlements because of the threat they pose to the peace 
process. 
  Answering a question about the massacre's effect on the 
peace 
talks between the Palestinians and Israel, which have already 
made significant progress, the Palestinian official said that 
such attacks certainly affect the peace process and demonstrate 
Israel's lack of credibility. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

