<H4>   PFLP-GC Official Criticizes 'Arafat </H4>
<F P=102> JN2802103694 Damascus SANA in Arabic 0830 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2802103694 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus SANA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Damascus, 28 Feb (SANA)-- Dr. Talal Naji, 
assistant secretary general of the Popular Front for the 
Liberation of Palestine-General Command [PFLP-GC], has stated 
that the heinous crime in the Ibrahimi Mosque in Hebron shows 
the Zionist enemy's hatred of the Arab and Islamic nation. 
  Interviewed by the newspaper TISHRIN today, Naji said that 
by 
this vile, hideous crime, the Zionists have proved their racist, 
Nazi, and fascist mentality. He demanded the world to uphold 
justice, human rights, and the right to self-determination. He 
expressed surprise that the United States was satisfied with the 
issuance of condemnation statements despite the ugliness of the 
massacre at a time when it would raise a hue and cry if the dead 
were Jews. He called on the international community to press 
for an immediate Israeli withdrawal from the occupied 
territories and to impose sanctions on Israel for not complying 
with the international legitimacy resolutions and charters. 
  Dr. Naji criticized Yasir 'Arafat for making concessions to 
Israel and said that 'Arafat's policy encourages the Zionist 
enemy and gives it the green light. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

