<H3> <TI>   `Hardline' Groups Vow `Revenge' for Massacre </TI></H3>
<H4>   PFLP, PLF, Hamas Hold U.S., PLO Responsible </H4>
<F P=102> JN2602142194 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1210 GMT 26 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2602142194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] George Habash, secretary general of the Popular 
Front for the Liberation of Palestine [PFLP], has said the basic 
lesson learned from the black criminal act is the direct 
responsibility the leaders of Israel hold at a time when they 
are talking about peace and security. Habash also held the U.S. 
Administration responsible through its protection of Israel. 
Habash did not exempt Yasir 'Arafat and the Oslo-Cairo team, as 
he said, from responsibility through their signing of agreements 
that entrench the occupation and protect the settlements. 
  In a statement published in the Iraqi newspaper 
AL-JUMHURIYAH, Abu-al-'Abbas [Muhammad 'Abbas], secretary 
general of the Palestine Liberation Front [PLF], called for 
halting the negotiations with Israel and resuming armed struggle. 
  Through its official spokesman Ibrahim Ghawash, who spoke at 
a news conference, Hamas called on the PLO to return to its 
people. Hamas criticized the president of the PLO for continuing 
negotiations. Hamas reiterated its rejection of the Oslo-Cairo 
agreements and said these agreements maintain the settlements as 
time bombs that explode in the faces of Palestinians every day. 

</TEXT>

