<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Contacts Made To Convene Fatah Revolutionary Council </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2802110094 Amman AL-DUSTUR in Arabic 28 Feb 94 p 32 </F>
<F P=103> JN2802110094 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-DUSTUR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Amman -- Well-informed Palestinian sources have 
stated that several Fatah leaders and cadres are holding 
consultations among themselves to convene Fatah' Revolutionary 
Council to discuss the situation in the Palestinian arena in 
light of the recent developments in the occupied territories and 
the bloody massacre committed by the Rabin government against 
worshipers in the Ibrahimi Mosque in Hebron. 
  A Fatah source told AL-DUSTUR that there are undeclared real 
divisions in the Fatah Movement ranks, the most acute of which 
is that the Fatah command outside the territories has lost 
control over the Fatah strike forces in the occupied territories 
which call for suspending the negotiations with Israel. 
  The sources added that several Fatah military officials 
might 
announce stands completely different from Palestinian President 
Yasir 'Arafat's stands if the Revolutionary Council does not 
convene. 

</TEXT>

