<H3> <TI>   Party Urges Protection of Palestinians, Halt to Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2702165194 Damascus SANA in Arabic 1550 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2702165194 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus SANA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Damascus, 27 Feb (SANA)--The Political Bureau of 
the Palestinian People's Party [PPP] has demanded a halt to the 
Palestinian-Israeli negotiations until international protection 
is provided for Palestinian citizens in reply to the heinous 
massacre perpetrated at the holy Ibrahimi Mosque where innocent 
worshipers from the Palestinian people's sons fell as victims. 
  In a statement issued here today, the PPP held the Israeli 
Government responsible for the massacre. This government 
facilitated the building of settlements for these criminals, 
armed them, and was lenient toward their previous crimes, such 
as what happened with the perpetrators of the al-Aqsa Mosque and 
the Hebron university massacres. 
  The PPP added that the Israeli Government cannot guarantee 
the Palestinian citizens' security. In fact, it joins in 
inflicting more Palestinian casualties and punishes their 
kinsfolk by firing at them and imposing collective punishments 
on them. 
  The PPP pointed out that such a situation cannot help 
achieve 
peace. It demanded that negotiations should be suspended until 
fair conditions conforming to the resolutions of international 
legitimacy are in place. 

</TEXT>

