<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Sa'iqah: Hebron `Crime' Result of Oslo Accord </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2602204694 (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2602204694 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The general command of the Organization of the 
Vanguards of the Popular Liberation War, al-Sa'iqah Forces, has 
issued as statement, which said: The Zionist enemy forces 
perpetrated an abhorrent crime at the Ibrahimi Mosque, adding a 
fresh outrage to its long list of crimes to promote its 
genocidal policy against our Arab people and liquidate their 
national cause. 
  This new Zionist crime is a natural corollary of the 
capitulatory agreement signed by 'Arafat with the Zionists in 
Oslo and Cairo and a consequence of the policies of 
relinquishment and capitulation pursued by 'Arafat and his 
deviationist methods. 
  We promise our people to remain faithful to our cause and 
national struggle and the martyrs' blood until all Palestinian 
territory is liberated. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

