<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Reacts to Attack at Hebron Mosque </TI></H3>
<H4>   House Condemns `Mournful Event' </H4>
<F P=102> JN2602172794 Amman PETRA-JNA in Arabic 1555 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2602172794 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman PETRA-JNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Amman, 26 Feb (PETRA) -- The House of 
Representatives has condemned the massacre during dawn prayers 
at the Ibrahimi Mosque in Hebron yesterday. This took place at 
the extraordinary session the House held this afternoon under 
Speaker Tahir al-Masri, atttended by Prime Minister Dr. 
'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali, to discuss the results of the 
reprehensible massacre Zionist extremists carried out against 
defenseless worshipers in the Ibrahimi Mosque. 
  At the start of the session, al-Masri said yesterday's 
incident is a mournful and momentous event. Although what the 
Zionists had perpetrated against the people in Hebron is not the 
first of its kind that the Palestinians and Muslims have 
experienced at the hands of the Zionist aggressors, the manner 
in which it was carried out, in a safe and sacred place, adds to 
the harm done to one's sentiments and makes it stand out as a 
very strange incident. 
  Al-Masri added: If our relatives in the occupied territories 
cannot be safe in their mosques and during their prayers, then 
where can they be safe? 

</TEXT>

